-------------------------
Grid box
-------------------------
1. columns and row
2. Properties
3. minmax()
4. grid areas
-------------------------
1. columns and row
-------------------------
> fr => fraction unit (Responsive)

> grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr 1fr;
  gird-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
  [ 1 ][ 2 ][ 3 ][ 4 ]
  

> grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
  [  1  ][  2  ]
  
> grid-template-columns:1fr 2fr;
  [  1  ][     2     ]
  
> grid-template-rows:1fr 1fr;
  |	1	|
  |	2	|	

> grid-template-rows:1fr 2fr;
  |	1	|
  |		|	
  |	2	|
  |		|
  
> Example:
-------------------------
HTML
-------------------------
<div class="grid-box">
  <div>1</div>
  <div>2</div>
  <div>3</div>
  <div>4</div>
</div>
-------------------------
CSS
-------------------------
grid-box{
 display:grid;
 grid-template-columns:1fr 3fr;
 grid-template-rows:1fr 3fr;
}  
_________________________
|___1____|_______2_______|
|	 |		  |
|   3    |       4       |
|________|_______________|


-------------------------
2. Properties
-------------------------
I.   justify-content (Horizontal Align to all content)
II.  align-content   (vertial Align to all content)
III. justify-items   (Horizontal Align to each element)
IV.  align-items     (vertial Align to each element)

V.   grid-auto-flow: dense; // use for image gallery


-------------------------
3. minmax()
-------------------------
{
 height:100%;
 display:grid;
 gird-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr);
}

> auto-fit  => Item takes remaining screen.
> auto-fill => keep remaining space.


-------------------------
4. grid areas
Example:1
-------------------------
<div class="grid-box">
  <div class="h">Header</div>
  <div class="n">Navbar</div>
  <div class="c">Content</div>
  <div class="f">Footer</div>
</div>
   
<style> 
.grid-box{
  display:grid;
  grid-template-columns:repeat(4, 1fr);
  grid-template-areas:
  "h h h h"
  "n c c c"
  "f f f f";
}
.h{
  grid-area:h;
 }
.n{
  grid-area:n;
}
.c{
  grid-area:c;
}
.f{
 grid-area:f;
}
</style> 

-------------------------
Example:2 with color
-------------------------
<div class="grid-box">
  <div class="h">Header</div>
  <div class="n">Navbar</div>
  <div class="c">Content</div>
  <div class="f">Footer</div>
</div>
   
<style> 
.grid-box{
  height:100vh;
  display:grid;
  grid-template-columns:repeat(4, 1fr);
  grid-template-rows:50px auto 50px;
  grid-template-areas:
  "h h h h"
  "n c c c"
  "f f f f";
}
@media(min-width:767px){
  .grid-box{
    grid-template-areas:
    "f f f f"
    "n c c c"
    "h h h h";
  }
}
.h{
  grid-area:h;
  background:#f00;
 }
.n{
  grid-area:n;
  background:#ddd;
}
.c{
  grid-area:c;
  background:#0f0;
}
.f{
 grid-area:f;
 background:#ccc;
}
</style> 	







